<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,1776,2017]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1776,1801]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Dorsum brown gray, underside white with a distinct line of demarcation. Distinct white patches behind ears and above eye present (
<figureCitation box="[476,591,1812,1837]" captionStart="FIGURE 41" captionStartId="38.[151,250,954,976]" captionTargetBox="[226,1360,193,932]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[226,1360,193,932]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 41. Wagner's gerbil, gerbillus dasyurus (photo by Mohammad AbuBaker)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202857/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figure 41</figureCitation>
). Soles of hind feet devoid of hair. Bases of hair, above tail, grayish. Tail long, covered with hair and terminating with a pencil. Four pairs of mammae. Skull of this species is very similar in size to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[321,421,1885,1908]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">
<emphasis box="[321,421,1885,1908]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">G. nanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, clearly distinguished by its smaller tympanic bulla (GSL between 26.4–30.1, TBL 8.1–10.4, TBW 
<quantity box="[394,506,1920,1945]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" unit="mm" value="4.6" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="4.0">4–5.2mm</quantity>
). Posterior margin of mastoid chamber never extends to the level of supraoccipital bone. Posterior mastoid chamber small. Zygomatic arches slender and delicate. Posterior occipital bone slightly constricted. Inferior posterior mastoid chamber extends down to the paraoccipital process (
<figureCitation box="[1168,1281,1992,2017]" captionStart="FIGURE 42" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1654,1676]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,613,1633]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[264,1323,613,1633]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 42. A. Dorsal,B. Ventral, C. Lateral views of the skull, and D. Upper maxillary teeth for Gerbillus dasyurus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202859/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Figure 42</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1017,954,976]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202857/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" startId="38.[151,250,954,976]" targetBox="[226,1360,193,932]" targetPageId="38">
